<setup>

  <selectFromSequence assignNames="a" from="2" to="5" step="1" numToSelect="1"/>  
  <selectFromSequence assignNames="b" from="3" to="8" step="1" numToSelect="1"/>    
  <selectFromSequence assignNames="c" from="1" to="4" step="1" numToSelect="1"/> 
  
  <function name="g" symbolic="true">-$a x^2 - $b x + $c</function>
  <derivative name="gP" symbolic="true">$g</derivative>  

  <function name="f" symbolic="true">$a/(x + $b) - $c</function>
  <derivative name="fP" symbolic="true">$f</derivative>  
  
</setup>

  <p>Use the limit definition to find the exact derivative value requested.</p>
  <ol marker="a.">
    <li>
      <p>If <m>g(x) = <math simplify>$$g(x)</math></m>, then <m>g'(<math simplify>$b-$a</math>) = </m><answer><award> $$gP($b - $a)</award></answer>.</p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>If <m>f(x) = <math simplify>$$f(x)</math></m>, then <m>f'(<math simplify>$b-2*$a</math>) = </m><answer><award> $$fP($b - 2*$a)</award></answer>.</p>
    </li>
  </ol>